reviews.review: Amazing!!! Critics are smoking too much

People are TRIPPIN. This movie is great. From a die hard Star Wars fan, I will be paying to see it more than once in the theater. Super fast fast and 2.5 hours long...so much packed into it, I have to rewatch it. People are being hyper critical of a movie meant for kids, and some of the best special effects in movie history. Better acting than the old Star Wars films we grew up on, tons of original cast cameos, twists and shocking ending. The message is clear, the future is in the hands of the youth. Older cast supports as mentors but itâ€™s all about the new heroes while respecting the past.

I don't know how to feel. While the movie was okay, it left points making me wonder what they were trying to do. 

It felt like they took elements of Return of the Jedi and copied and pasted and just added new pizzaz. I am a bit disappointed, but also somewhat happy. They could have done better in my opinion and they could have done a lot worse.

Let the Skywalker legacy die with this movie. Move on to something else. Explore the Old Republic, do something else. Leave this time period alone. It's been beaten to death and back.
good visuals, much of the action scenes did not make alot of sense for being a star wars movie, quite confusing story arc in the trilogy that didn't really get finished
Great movie! A great conclusion that to the end of a great trilogy! A must see!
Great addition to the series of Star Wars movies! Well done!

As the final Episode to a saga that has spanned 42 years, The Rise of Skywalker is a perfect fit after the broken piece that was Last Jedi.
Episode 9 was emotional, exciting, dramatic, funny and a thrill ride from start to finish...go and enjoy The Rise of Skywalker...it was worth the forty-two year wait !!!!
I enjoyed it, for the most part. There were a couple things that disappointed me, but I definitely liked it better than The Last Jedi.
